<br>
I am Sinrice a Grave Queen, former Shadowknight of the 60th season.  Bestill your fear for let my power not scare you...In truth I have let go of my ways of the hunt and wish only to speak and regail those who wish to partake of my experience in this, the land of Everquest.<br>
<br>
*removes hood and cloak to reveal tattered clothes...an empty sword sheath...and what appears to be remains of rations...the skin is rough and scars are abound...whatever beauty that once existed has seen the toll of many battles*<br>
<br>
Aye, in retrospect do I regret anything?  Have not thought much of the past...I have spent much time calming the hatred that flows in my veins...the same hatred that once would have fuelled an arduous and agonizing death for all of you innocents...*a gleam of madness in her eyes is quickly subdued*<br>
<br>
I will tell my tale as you wish but bear with me...my age has weakened me much but I will rise as often as my mortal remains to continue.<br>
<br>
Aye, was many seasons ago that I began this hunt in Freeport, the city of men.  Had I foreseen what I was to become I would have...never mind, no sense in pouring over the past.  I was a child of the streets...living on what I could find from the lowliest of rat meat to the meals that I would be tossed...or stolen...or seized.  I suppose it was my fate that on a particular full moon night, as rains poured from the heavens, I stumbled all alone into an abandoned building seeking shelter from the cold and empty streets, save for the single dark-elf girl who had been at the same spot for ages.  Odd that I was wearing the same tattered robes I wear now...<br>
<br>
*a single tear rolls down her cheek...and then boils off much to gasps of amazement by the crowd*<br>
<br>
I could have chosen the Leather shop or even the bar - scoundrels there would have been most paying to spend time with me but, no I chose an abandoned building.<br>
<br>
As I wandered deeper within, I could see glows, fire, and other terrifying sights emanating from deep down.  I ventured forward, coming upon numerous figures in the dark and that was where I met Netuk Phenzon, whose cold hand had grabbed me aside in a bone-chilling grip.<br>
<br>
He muttered only two words - Die child - and I thought that my world was at an end...how glorious that might have been.  Regardless, as he drew his sword a bolt of pure malevolence forced him back - thrusting his sword into my hands.  Indeed, it was heavy but enticing with dried blood adorning its blade.<br>
<br>
A voice pierced the darkness - How does that weapon feel child?<br>
<br>
I did not answered.  I chose instead to let actions be my answer and proceeded to drive the blade into the skull of Netuk, who was lying on the floor stunned by that unknown force.  I even rubbed my hand in the blood that emerged for, at the time, it was a strange calming effect on my newfound rage.<br>
<br>
The same voice - Zhem, tend to Netuk.  Child, do you wish to serve Innoruuk, Lord of Hate?<br>
<br>
I responded - Will he help me rise?  I only wish to leave the streets...<br>
<br>
The voice - No.  He will not - you are of no important to him.  We of Dismal Rage, on the other hand, follow him for many reasons - with us, you will kill in his name...and you will grow powerful indeed...with magic as well to your aid...<br>
<br>
I remember staring at the blood, the sword, and then at Zhem who had already begun to revice Netuk.  All I said was - Will killing be my purpose?<br>
<br>
Voice - Yes, you will kill all...eventually<br>
<br>
Myself - Including Innoruuk?<br>
<br>
Many bursts of laughter came forth from the shadows.  Zhem paused in his work.<br>
<br>
Voice - Welcome child to the immense power of hate.<br>
<br>
Out stepped Pietro Zarn and my training was to begin.  As I was to learn, the power of the shadowknight lay not only in the might of weaponry but also in the ancient art of magic, whose essence of mana was not the easiest knowledge to learn....<br>
<br>
But I must rest for I am tired - I will continue when possible.  I pray that should you be visited by the gods when you sleep, may your death be quick and painless - let Innoruuk not enjoy that at the very least..<br>
<br>
*Murmurs of the crowd.  All disperse swiftly save a solitary seated child...quite awake indeed)<br>
<br>
(ooc Hell if I know when/whether or not to continue - thanks for reading so far though lol - thats an achievement by itself.  I havent even begun the hunt =P and the deaths...ugh.  Open to comments.  Stay safe in EQ all)<br>
